parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, loss of critical vehicle functions, and accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire
especially in the passenger seat or center console area
electrical components malfunction
lights quit working
turn signal relay energizes and de-energizes rapidly
brake pedal release triggers unusual sounds
and electrical system malfunctions causing loss of visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the vehicle can cause corrosion, electrical system failures, and fires, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Passenger floor accumulates large amounts of water
battery compartment and rear floorboard are filled with water
door locks malfunction due to corrosion
and wiring and connectors are corroded and shorted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition/anti-theft system failures can cause distractions, accidents, or injuries, and may lead to vehicle theft or unauthorized access.
symptoms: Door locks malfunction
automatic door locks suddenly and unexpectedly lock
and ignition/anti-theft system malfunctions causing distractions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake gasket can cause engine performance issues, including shaking, strong fume smells, and the service engine light to come on. If left unrepaired, it can lead to more severe problems, such as lifter damage, and potentially cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: Engine shaking
strong fume smells
service engine light comes on
engine performance issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine coolant leakage can cause overheating, engine damage, and potentially lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
engine overheating
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingestion into the engine can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement.
symptoms: Engine lock-up
engine failure
water in air hoses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering column becomes loose internally
the steering column needs to be removed to tighten the bolts that hold the column assembly together
the car cannot make left turns
the steering fails while turning
the steering vibrates when applying the brakes
a popping noise is heard from the front end of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering loses power at low speeds
the steering vibrates when applying the brakes
a popping noise is heard from the front end of the car.
